Program: Discovery
Title: Living beyond our means
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry44
Last Broadcast Date: 02 July 2002
Are we asking more of nature than it can provide? The world has limited resources, and with a growing population we are expecting more of it than ever before. Deforestation, rising sea levels, urbanisation, more rainfall and wind could all place unrealistic demands on the planet.